      <prov id="DLM35268" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">104</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Refusal to grant recognition<struckoutwords/></heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If the Director-General proposes to refuse to grant recognition<struckoutwords/> for the functions and activities applied for, the Director-General must give the applicant—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>a notice containing such particulars as will clearly inform the applicant of the substance of the grounds on which the Director-General proposes to refuse to recognise<struckoutwords/> the applicant; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>a copy (or adequate summary) of any information on which the Director-General relies in proposing to refuse to grant recognition<struckoutwords/>; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>a reasonable opportunity to make written submissions or be heard in respect of the matter.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Where the Director-General finally determines to refuse to grant recognition<struckoutwords/>, the Director-General must as soon as practicable notify that fact to the applicant in writing, giving reasons.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If a person acting under the delegated authority of the Director-General refuses to grant recognition<struckoutwords/>, the applicant may seek a review of that decision under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM36111">section 162</intref></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
