      <prov id="DLM35281" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">106</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Duties of recognised agencies</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>In undertaking the specified functions and activities for which it is recognised, a recognised agency has the following duties:</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>it must ensure that all <insertwords>recognised</insertwords> persons employed or engaged or used by it are not placed in positions or situations that compromise their impartiality and independence in relation to the performance of their functions and duties under this Act:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>it must ensure that it is adequately resourced and that systems are maintained to ensure that its functions and activities under this Act are carried out properly.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM35282"><amended-provision>Section 106(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 June 2005</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM338037">section 5(8)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Animal Products Amendment Act 2005</amending-leg> (2005 No 26).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM35283" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">107</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Duties of <insertwords>recognised</insertwords> persons</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>In carrying out the specified functions and activities for which he or she is <insertwords>recognised, a recognised</insertwords> person has the following duties:</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>to undertake only those functions and activities as <insertwords>a recognised</insertwords> person under this Act that are conferred on them by the Director-General:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>to comply with the relevant requirements of any regulations or specifications in force from time to time under this Act, and any directions given by the Director-General under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM35207">section 81</intref></citation>:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>to maintain an appropriate degree of impartiality and independence in carrying out their functions and activities in accordance with the <insertwords>recognition</insertwords> conferred by the Director-General:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">d</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>to maintain appropriate confidentiality (particularly in relation to commercially sensitive matters) relating to operations and activities they come into contact with in the course of carrying out their functions and activities under this Act (except to the extent required to report under paragraph (e) or otherwise for the purposes of this Act), including matters relating to design, technology, systems, and practices:</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">e</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>to report to an appropriate Ministry official, in accordance with the requirements imposed by or under this Act,—</text>
                  <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">i</label>
                    <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <text>any failure to comply with, or any inadequacy in, a risk management programme:</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ii</label>
                    <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <text>any failure to comply with a regulated control scheme:</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                  <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                    <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">iii</label>
                    <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                      <text>any other matter which is required by or under this Act to be reported on by <insertwords>recognised</insertwords> persons of the relevant type:</text>
                    </para>
                  </label-para>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">f</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>in the case of <insertwords>a recognised</insertwords> risk management programme verifier, to be under the management of a recognised risk management programme verifying agency.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM35284"><amended-provision>Section 107 heading</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 June 2005</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM338037">section 5(8)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Animal Products Amendment Act 2005</amending-leg> (2005 No 26).</history-note>
